== b) Discuss the key features of the distributions. How does the spread of AABW occur in the Atlantic, Pacific, and Indian Oceans?
flows into all three aligned ocean basins. 
The majority of 57% is discharged into the Pacific Ocean, 37% into the Atlantic Ocean and the remaining 5% into the Indian Ocean.
Johnson, 2008 reckoned that 36% of the total ocean volume is made up of AABW.
More than 80% of the AABW formed in the Weddel Sea and along the eastern Antarctic continent are exported into the Atlantic Ocean.
While more than 90% from the Ross Sea are exported into the Pacific Ocean. (Solodoch et al., 2022)

The AABW is moving northwards mostly in the western parts of the ocean basins, as can be seen in the maps for this exercise.
As it has such a high density it flows as deep as possible along the bathymetry.
It cannot cross for example the mid atlantic ridge, however, regions of steep gradients in topography are regions of increased mixing with the waters above.

